The president told advisers that Mr. Rosenstein assured him at the time that the Cohen investigation had nothing to do with him.
Since then, Mr. Trump has asked his advisers if Mr. Rosenstein was deliberately misleading him to keep him calm.
Mr. Trump was now battling twin investigations that seemed to be moving ever close to him.
He called Mr. Cohen a “rat.” The messages infuriated Democratic lawmakers, who claimed the president was trying to threaten and intimidate a witness before testimony Mr. Cohen planned before Congress.
